.TH raveloxmidi-stream "1"
.SH NAME
raveloxmidi-stream @VERSION@ \- raw MIDI stream bridge for raveloxmidi
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBraveloxmidi-stream\fP \-\-bind-address \fIaddress\fP [\-\-input \fI-\fP|\fIpath\fP] [\-\-output \fI-\fP|\fIpath\fP] [options]

\fBraveloxmidi-stream\fP \-\-config \fIfilename\fP [\-\-input \fI-\fP|\fIpath\fP] [\-\-output \fI-\fP|\fIpath\fP] [options]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.BR raveloxmidi-stream
bridges simple binary MIDI streams to and from the raveloxmidi RTP-MIDI service.
It can read outgoing MIDI messages from stdin or a named pipe, and it can write
received MIDI events to stdout or a named pipe.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -c, --config \fIfilename\fP
Name of configuration file to use.
.br
The timing configuration items documented in \fBraveloxmidi\fP(1), including
\fBtiming.enabled\fP and \fBtiming.playout_delay_ms\fP, also apply to inbound
RTP-MIDI events written by this utility.
.TP
.B -b, --bind-address \fIaddress\fP
Set the raveloxmidi \fBnetwork.bind_address\fP configuration item.
.TP
.B -i, --input \fI-\fP|\fIpath\fP
Read outgoing raw MIDI bytes from stdin or the given file or named pipe.
.TP
.B -o, --output \fI-\fP|\fIpath\fP
Write received raw MIDI bytes to stdout or the given file or named pipe.
.TP
.B -d, --debug
Enable debug logging.
.TP
.B -v, --version
Display current version number and exit.
.TP
.B -h, --help
Display help information.
.SH STREAM FORMAT
The stream format is a sequence of ordinary MIDI messages. Each message must
include its status byte. Running status is not supported.
.LP
System Exclusive messages are framed as \fB0xF0 payload... 0xF7\fP. Complete
frames are accepted up to the \fBstream.max_sysex_size\fP configuration limit.
Large frames are segmented for RTP-MIDI transport and reconstructed on output.
Unterminated or oversized frames are discarded.
.LP
Examples:
.LP
Note On is encoded as status, note, velocity:
.LP
\fB0x90 0x3c 0x64\fP
.LP
Program Change is encoded as status, program:
.LP
\fB0xc0 0x05\fP
.LP
See \fBdocs/STREAM_CLI.md\fP in the source tree for the complete stream format
and named pipe workflow examples.
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBraveloxmidi\fP(1)
